The only documentation of the custom settings/type system for H1 modules is:

- this section of the H1 developer manual:
   http://crawler.archive.org/articles/developer_manual/settings.html

- the classes/class-comments themselves

It&#39;s not clear where your getAttrValue() code is running, nor even where 
the getAttrValue() method comes from. (It does not appear to be an 
accessor inherited from our settings-related supertypes.) If you follow 
the conventions of the existing classes and only try to read the 
attributes at the same time as the existing classes, you should get the 
same access to XML-set values.

However, if you are the the point of adding your own components, you may 
find it worthwhile to move to H3. Configuration XML is of the same 
format of the Spring container system, and modules are just beans, with 
typical bean property accessors. While there&#39;s a bit less 
configuration-guidance in the web UI -- you have to edit XML directly -- 
it sounds like you&#39;ve already embraced that change. It should be an 
easier base to extend.

Hope this helps,

- Gordon @ IA

